==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[spoliatio]]''

===Noun===
'''spoliation'''

# The act of [[plunder]]ing or [[spoil]]ing; [[robbery]]; [[deprivation]]; [[despoliation]].
# Robbery or plunder in times of [[war]]; especially, the [[authorize]]d act or practice of plundering [[neutral]]s at sea.
# {{law}} The [[intentional]] [[destruction]] of or [[tamper]]ing with (a document) in such way as to [[impair]] [[evidentiary]] effect.

